<DESCRIPT>  BRIEF  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  SHUTTLE bus service is available from the Curtner light-rail station to the
Santa Clara County Fair.;    Fairgoers can take light rail to the Curtner
station, then transfer to the Line 26 shuttle bus to the fairgrounds.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Local  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  TAKE A BUS TO THE FAIR FROM TROLLEY  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  The Valley Log;  SETTING THE RECORD STRAIGHT (publ. 7/29/91, pg. 2B);  An item
in Friday's Valley Log incorrectly reported details of discounts for bus and
light-rail passengers to the Santa Clara County Fair. Such passengers will
receive coupons for $2 off the fair admission price, valid only from noon to 5
p.m. Tuesday through Friday, and coupons for $2 off the $9 all-you- can-ride
offer, valid for the same period.  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     The weekday shuttle schedule will be every 15 minutes from 10:30 a.m. to 9
p.m. and every 30 minutes from 9 to 11:15 p.m. On weekends, the shuttle will
run every 15 minutes from 10 a.m. to 7 p.m., every 20 minutes from 7 to 9 p.m.
and every 30 minutes from 9 to 11 p.m.;    Buses on lines 66, 68 and 73 also
go to the fairgrounds.;    Bus and light-rail passengers will receive coupons
good for discounts of $2 on the fair admission price and $2 on carnival
rides.;    For information, call (408) 287-4210 from most of Santa Clara
County, (415) 965-3100 from Palo Alto or (408) 683-4151 from South County.
Call (408) 299-4848 for the Teleprinter for the hearing-impaired.; COMING;
FREE FESTIVAL OF MUSIC SET;     A free festival featuring music, refreshments,
T-shirt gifts and door prizes is scheduled from 11:30 a.m. to 6 p.m. Saturday
at Guitar Showcase, 3090 S. Bascom Ave., San Jose.;    Music will be provided
by several groups, including the Robert Berry Band and the Christine Amber
Band. Proceeds from a raffle will go to a San Jose child abuse treatment
center.;    (hbox);    The Humane Society of Santa Clara Valley is reminding
visitors of the Gilroy Garlic Festival today through Sunday that it will
maintain an emergency animal shelter at the festival gate.;    If necessary to
safeguard the animals' health, Humane Society workers will remove them from
parked vehicles and place them in the shelter. Animals not claimed by the end
of the day will be taken to the Humane Society in Santa Clara.;    (hbox);   
An "All-You-Can-Eat Ice Cream Social" is scheduled from 1:30 to 4:30 p.m.
Sunday at the Community School of Music and Arts in Mountain View as a
fund-raiser for the school, at 253 Martens Ave., near Grant Road.;    The
event will include a variety of sweet treats, a children's art exhibit, art
activities, and a "sound sampler," in which children can try playing several
musical instruments. Tickets cost $5 for adults and $3 for children. Call
(415) 961-0342 for information.  </TEXT>
